The paper focuses on deep learning models for question answering, which is a task that falls under natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper explores models with memory components and attention mechanisms, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also uses simulated data, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) depending on the nature of the data.
